Comics (narrative art form) The Justice League of America preceded the Avengers by over three years. The first appearance of the Justice League of America in comics was in The Brave and the Bold #28 in March 1960. The iconic cover featured five heroes battling Starro the Conqueror. In November 1960, the League got its own series, with the first appearance of the supervillain Despero.
